THE family of the 24-year-old DJ wants answers. Chris Thobakgale was found dead in police holding cells a day after he was arrested and detained at Lenyenye Police Station. Better known as DJ Lezozo, Chris was arrested last Friday with two friends – Fanie Mabunda (29) and Tebogo Pilusa (24). if(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");<a href="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/jump?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" target="_blank"><img src="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/ad?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" border="0" alt=""></a>They were accused of stealing booze at a local tavern in Pulaneng Village outside Tzaneen, Limpopo. His mum, Sesonkwane (54), said she was expecting that her son would get bail and come back home within a few days.“Something is not adding up,” she said.“The police came here on the day he died and told the family that he had complained of stomach pain. “My question is: why didn’t they take him to hospital? I refuse to lose my son like this.“Someone has to pay for this. I need answers,” she said.“He had bruises all over his face. I want to know what happened.”Fanie said he and DJ Lezozo were placed in a single cell on Friday evening. “He was removed from the cell on Saturday morning after complaining of stomach pain. “We were shocked when we were told that afternoon he had died,” said Fanie.He said it all started when they were approached by a cop and an unknown woman at a local tavern.“They told us to get into the police van and when we arrived at the cop shop, the police accused us of stealing booze from a tavern,” he said.Independent Police Investigative Directorate spokesman Moses Dlamini said the matter was reported to them. “An investigation is underway. Our investigators have already visited the station to determine what happened.“We also need to investigate circumstances surrounding his death,” said Dlamini.